      "content": {
        "text": "Then as w = vr, v = w/r so that Energy = (1/2)mv^2 + (1/2)I(v/r)^2. As I, m are constant and r decreases, if v is constant Energy will increase. So v has to decrease for Energy to stay constant. As Energy is conserved, v decreases. Correct or no?"
